SIMPLE: plenteous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plenteous
<hw>Plen"te*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Plenty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Containing plenty; abundant;
copious; plentiful; sufficient for every purpose; <as>as, a
<ex>plenteous</ex> supply</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Reaping
<xex>plenteous</xex> crop.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Yielding abundance; productive; fruitful.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The seven <xex>plenteous</xex> years.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Gen. xli.
34.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having plenty; abounding; rich.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Lord shall make thee <qex>plenteous</qex> in goods.</q>
<rj><qau>Deut. xxviii. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Plentiful; copious; full. <er>See
Ample</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Plen"te*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Plen"te*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plentevous</ent>⟦br⟧
